 NDLEA PHOTO: Twitter  Recall that the agency last week arrested seven drugs barons operating four large warehouses in Ukpuje forest, Owan council of Edo State, where a total of 16,344 bags of cannabis and seeds weighing 233, 778 kilogram were seized, in addition to two pump-action and one double-barrel guns. The estimated street value of the seized illicit drug was put at over N1.4bn. Giving a breakdown of the Benue drug seizure while briefing the Chairman/ Chief Executive of the anti-drug agency, Brig. Gen. (rtd) Mohamed Buba Marwa, the state commander of NDLEA, Mrs. Florence Ezeonye, said the bags of cannabis seized during the operation weighs 1,578 kilograms. Ezeonye said: “Operatives of the NDLEA Benue State command intercepted in Makurdi, an empty trailer from Awka, Anambra State heading to Lafia, Nasarawa State, when properly searched, 600 blocks of compressed cannabis Sativa weighing 600kg were discovered in a compartment constructed under the flat belly of the truck. The mode of concealment was first of its kind. “Another seizure was made when our men stormed a warehouse filled with drugs harvested by some farmers at the suburb of Guma council. The total number of illicit drug evacuated from the warehouse weighs 978kg. The drug dealers shot at my men on sighting them, but their attack was repelled and as such, we did not record any casualty.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .